		<itunes:subtitle>After a 14-month hiatus, we dust off Just One More Book to participate in the Canadian National Day of Podcasting, a virtual event intended to bring stale shows out of retirement for one-day in a festival-like reunion of online content creators. - </itunes:subtitle>
		<itunes:summary>After a 14-month hiatus, we dust off Just One More Book to participate in the Canadian National Day of Podcasting, a virtual event intended to bring stale shows out of retirement for one-day in a festival-like reunion of online content creators.

In this episode, we highlight some of the chapter books we've read since parking JOMB last year.

Andrea's picks

	Ribblestrop by Andy Mulligan
	After Hamelin by Bill Richardson
	Elijah Buxton by Christopher Paul Curtis

Mark's picks

	The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy by Douglas Adams
	Kendra Kandlestar and the Crack in Kazah (the first draft of the next book in the series) by Lee Edward Fodi</itunes:summary>
