		<item>
		<title>Back in the Saddle</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/JustOneMoreBook/~3/f6EfEiDqEUI/</link>
		<comments>http://justonemorebook.com/2010/11/20/back-in-the-saddle/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 20 Nov 2010 18:47:38 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>justonemorebook@gmail.com (Mark Blevis and Andrea Ross)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Podcast]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://staging.justonemorebook.com/?p=1376</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[If Briefly. December 1, 2010 has been designated as Canadian National Day of Dusting Off Old Podcasts. JustOneMoreBook.com has been sitting dormant for 14 months now. I miss it. Mark misses it. Lucy and Bayla miss it. So, although we were completely unprepared and the audio itself is nothing to be proud of, it was [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://wecanrebuildher.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IMG_19915.jpg" target="_blank"><img class="size-medium wp-image-6661 alignright" style="margin: 0px; border: 0pt none;" title="IMG_19915" src="http://wecanrebuildher.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IMG_19915-225x300.jpg" alt="" width="95" height="126" /></a><a href="http://wecanrebuildher.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IMG_19923.jpg" target="_blank"><img class="size-medium wp-image-6659 alignright" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 0px;" title="IMG_19923" src="http://wecanrebuildher.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IMG_19923-225x300.jpg" alt="" width="95" height="126" /></a><strong>If Briefly.</strong></p>
<p>December 1, 2010 has been designated as <a title="Canadian National Day of Dusting Off Old Podcasts" href="http://www.markblevis.com/canadian-national-day-of-podcasting/" target="_blank">Canadian National Day of Dusting Off Old Podcasts</a>.</p>
<p><a title="Just One More Book! Children's Literacy/Literature Podcast" href="http://www.JustOneMoreBook.com/About" target="_blank">JustOneMoreBook.com</a> has been sitting dormant for 14 months now.</p>
<p>I miss it. Mark misses it. Lucy and Bayla miss it.</p>
<p>So, although we were completely unprepared and the audio itself is nothing to be proud of, it was huge fun to dust off that audio equipment,drink some delicious coffee in our cozy Wild Oat home, and chirp some off-the-cuff praise for a few children&#8217;s books.</p>
<p>Stay tuned for audio, December 1, 2010.</p>
<p><center><a href="http://wecanrebuildher.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IMG_19916.jpg" target="_blank"><img class="size-medium wp-image-6660 alignnone" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 0px;" title="IMG_19916" src="http://wecanrebuildher.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IMG_19916-225x300.jpg" alt="" width="95" height="126" /></a> <img class="size-medium wp-image-6657 alignnone" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 0px;" title="photo 1" src="http://wecanrebuildher.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/photo-14-e1290275499436-225x300.jpg" alt="" width="95" height="126" /> <img class="size-medium wp-image-6662 alignnone" style="margin: 0px; border: 0pt none;" title="IMG_19914" src="http://wecanrebuildher.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/11/IMG_19914-225x300.jpg" alt="" width="95" height="126" /></center></p>
