		<title>Wishing you a Happy, Healthy New Year … and many more to follow</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/JustOneMoreBook/~3/lvqGUiDUFq0/</link>
		<comments>http://justonemorebook.com/2009/12/24/wishing-you-a-happy-healthy-new-year-and-many-more-to-follow/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 24 Dec 2009 13:27:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>justonemorebook@gmail.com (Mark Blevis and Andrea Ross)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Podcast]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[new year]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[wishes]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.justonemorebook.com/?p=1343</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[As surreal as it continues to be, we are making our way through this unexpected Breast Cancer Journey thanks to the support, good wishes and strong positive vibes of our generous friends, family and online/offline community. Chemo is now underway and I believe Andrea is on the upswing of the first round. It&#8217;s an odd [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-1344" title="surgery2" src="http://www.justonemorebook.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/12/surgery2.jpg" alt="surgery2" />As surreal as it continues to be, we are making our way through this unexpected Breast Cancer Journey thanks to the support, good wishes and strong positive vibes of our generous friends, family and online/offline community.</p>
<p>Chemo is now underway and I believe Andrea is on the upswing of the first round. It&#8217;s an odd Christmas but we&#8217;re working towards many happy Christmas seasons to come.</p>
<p>We miss JOMB, the stories, authors, illustrators, listeners, the conversations. If you&#8217;d like to keep in touch, we&#8217;ve set up a Flickr photo journal <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/justonemorebook/sets/72157623031758514/">here </a>where you can check in on our progress and even leave us your thoughts.</p>
<p>Wishing each of you a very happy holiday season and a happy, healthy 2010 full of love, warmth and great memories.</p>
<p>Be well and be happy,<br />
Andrea, Mark, Lucy and Bayla<br />
xo</p>
