			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="alignright" title="Love for Reading" src="http://www.justonemorebook.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/06/gracie_220.jpg" alt="" width="220" height="220" />We opened our <a title="Love of Reading gallery" href="http://www.justonemorebook.com/love-of-reading-gallery" target="_blank">Love of Reading Gallery</a> in July 2008 and invited all illustrators to submit original artwork that promotes a love of reading.  Submissions came from as far as Brazil, Vietnam and South Africa and covered all age ranges.</p>
<p>On this edition, Mark speaks with artist, <a title="Bookie Woogie Book Review Blog" href="http://www.bookiewoogie.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">blogger</a> and budding author, <a title="CHICKEN NUGGET LEMON TOOTY" href="http://www.isaacgracelily.blogspot.com/" target="_blank">Gracie</a>, now 8 (she was 7 when she created her illustration) about <strong>Love for Reading</strong>, her contribution to our Love of Reading Gallery, her illustration technique and a book idea she has.</p>
<p>Be sure to enjoy all of the amazing artwork in our <a style="text-decoration: none; color: #6c3bca;" title="Love of Reading Gallery" href="http://www.justonemorebook.com/love-of-reading-gallery/" target="_blank">Love of Reading Gallery</a>.</p>
<p><em>Did you notice Gracie&#8217;s reference to <a title="HICCUPotamus" href="http://www.aaronzenz.com/about2.html" target="_blank">The HICCUPotamus</a></em> (<a title="The Hiccupotamus on JOMB" href="http://www.justonemorebook.com/2008/07/25/contagious-wordplaygious-the-hiccupotamus/" target="_self">on JOMB</a>)?</p>
